<subSubSection id="0BFC65213A24A05997A6B4966B09FEDF" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="435936AA3A24A05997A6B4966B09FEDF" blockId="6.[151,1436,150,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="7192EAB83A24A05997A6B4966F7BFF6F" bold="true" box="[199,315,186,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Remarks.</emphasis>
Live photos were taken by Shan Gui in Xinglong County, 
<collectingRegion id="8122F8483A24A05994A1B4966A2CFF6F" box="[960,1132,186,212]" country="China" name="Hebei" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Hebei Province</collectingRegion>
and in Miyun and Huairou, 
<collectingRegion id="8122F8483A24A05997F6B4F26EA9FF43" box="[151,233,222,248]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Beijing</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="DBDD2A2F3A24A059979DB4F26F03FF42" box="[252,323,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1627,1651]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,380,1600]" captionTargetId="figure-121@6.[151,1436,380,1604]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lomatia shanguii sp. nov. in: Miyun District, Beijing (a and c); Xinglong County, Hebei Province (b); Huairou District, Beijing (d). (Photos: Shan Gui)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5974186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5974186/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="84E64D293A24A05995D4B4F36DFAFF42" authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" box="[693,954,222,249]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belzebul">
<emphasis id="7192EAB83A24A05995D4B4F36D72FF43" box="[693,818,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">L. belzebul</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated by the wing mostly infuscated with darker areas close to veins, tergite 1 with basal half black and apical half yellow and with dense yellow hairs laterally and sparse yellow hairs medially. In 
<taxonomicName id="84E64D293A24A059945FB50B6A42FEFB" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[830,1026,294,320]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Proteaceae" genus="Lomatia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="belzebul">
<emphasis id="7192EAB83A24A059945FB50B6A42FEFB" box="[830,1026,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Lomatia belzebul</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the wing has only the anterior 1/4 infuscated, and the remainder parts hyaline; and tergite 1 is entirely black with the yellowish hairs laterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
